"io.exec: nonexistent binary returns result block with non-zero exit code. Uses --allow-io."

# Exit code for command-not-found varies by platform:
# Unix: 127 (POSIX convention), Windows: 1 or 9009 (cmd.exe)
` { target: :test requires-io: true }
test:
  { :io r: io.exec(["nonexistent-binary-xyz"]) }.(
    if(r.'exit-code' > 0,
      { RESULT: :PASS },
      { RESULT: :FAIL }))
